From: Mohammed Naser <mnaser@vexxhost.com>
Date: Fri, 3 Jul 2026 12:00:00 -0400
Subject: [PATCH] netlink-socket: Increase Netlink receive buffer to 16 MiB

Open vSwitch uses Netlink sockets to receive datapath upcalls from the
kernel. Flow setup can be bursty, so a short scheduling delay in userspace
can leave a large number of upcall messages queued on the receive socket.

Increase the requested receive buffer from 4 MiB to 16 MiB. Linux accounts
approximately twice the requested socket receive buffer size, so this gives
the upcall path materially more burst headroom while keeping the default
reasonable for deployments with per-CPU upcall dispatch enabled.

This follows the same mitigation pattern as upstream commits that raised
the Netlink receive buffer from the kernel default to 1 MiB and then from
1 MiB to 4 MiB.

Signed-off-by: Mohammed Naser <mnaser@vexxhost.com>
---
 lib/netlink-socket.c | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/lib/netlink-socket.c b/lib/netlink-socket.c
index 534bb5061..c79cd3b26 100644
--- a/lib/netlink-socket.c
+++ b/lib/netlink-socket.c
@@ -178,7 +178,7 @@ nl_sock_create(int protocol, struct nl_sock **sockp)
     sock->protocol = protocol;
     sock->next_seq = 1;
 
-    rcvbuf = 1024 * 1024 * 4;
+    rcvbuf = 1024 * 1024 * 16;
 #ifdef _WIN32
     sock->rcvbuf = rcvbuf;
     retval = get_sock_pid_from_kernel(sock);
-- 
2.34.1
